                <fr:title text="Levi-Civita symbol">Levi-Civita symbol</fr:title>
                <fr:taxon>definition</fr:taxon>
              </fr:frontmatter>
              <fr:mainmatter>
                <html:p>To prove properties about the determinant, it's helpful to introduce the <html:dfn>Levi-Civita symbol</html:dfn> which is a family of symbols usually denoted <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\varepsilon _{i_{1},…,i_{n}}]]></fr:tex> for some <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[n\in \mathbb {N}]]></fr:tex>.</html:p>
                <html:p>This is defined to be such that:</html:p>
                <html:ol><html:li><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\varepsilon _{1,2,3,…,n-1,n}=+1]]></fr:tex>, and</html:li>
<html:li>swapping two adjacent indices costs us a sign, in the sense that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\varepsilon _{i_{1},…,i_{j},i_{j+1},…,i_{n}}=-\varepsilon _{i_{1},…,i_{j+1},i_{j},…,i_{n}}]]></fr:tex></html:li></html:ol>
                <html:p>As a consequence of that second property, any repeated indices give us a zero (e.g., <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\varepsilon _{i,j,j}=0]]></fr:tex>).</html:p>
              </fr:mainmatter>
            </fr:tree>
            <fr:tree show-metadata="false">
              <fr:frontmatter>
                <fr:authors>
                  <fr:author>
                    <fr:link href="/alex-nelson/" title="Alex Nelson" uri="http://localhost:8000/alex-nelson/" display-uri="alex-nelson" type="local">Alex Nelson</fr:link>
